      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): add Authorization header to provider preflight probe",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThe cron job preflight check sends `GET {baseUrl}/models` to verify local provider connectivity before running a job, but was doing so **without an Authorization header**. For providers behind auth middleware (LiteLLM, vLLM, etc.), this generates spurious 401 errors on every cron run.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`model-preflight.runtime.ts` -> `probeLocalProviderEndpoint()` called `fetchWithSsrFGuard` with `init: { method: \"GET\" }` - no auth header.\n\n## Fix\n\n**Replaced hand-rolled auth resolution with `resolveApiKeyForProvider`** from the shared SDK auth runtime (`plugin-sdk/provider-auth-runtime.ts`). This reuses the full credential chain (config -> auth profiles -> env vars -> plugin hooks -> SecretRef) instead of a limited 3-source fallback.\n\n### What changed\n\n- `model-preflight.runtime.ts`: Removed hand-rolled `resolveProbeApiKey()`; added `resolveApiKeyForProvider` import; added `agentDir`/`workspaceDir` params; 2-tier auth: `request.auth.token` override -> `resolveApiKeyForProvider`; OAuth exclusion; auth leak protection via error redaction\n- `run.ts`: Passes `agentDir` and `workspaceDir` to the preflight call\n- `model-preflight.runtime.test.ts`: Expanded from 4 to 12 tests covering all auth paths\n\n### Auth precedence\n\n1. `request.auth.token` (explicit config override, `authorization-bearer` mode) - highest\n2. `resolveApiKeyForProvider` - full credential chain from the shared SDK runtime\n3. No auth (OAuth tokens excluded; missing credentials non-fatal)\n\n### Security\n\n- `Authorization: Bearer <key>` values are **redacted** from error messages via regex\n- OAuth tokens are never sent to reachability probes\n- SSRF protection via hostname allowlist + private network scoping\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Cron job preflight GET /models to local LiteLLM proxy returns 401 because no Authorization header is sent, causing \"No api key passed in\" errors on every cron run.\n\n- **Real environment tested:** OpenClaw 2026.5.18 (npm install, Oracle VPS, Ubuntu 24.04, Node.js v24.15.0). LiteLLM proxy at http://127.0.0.1:4000 configured in openclaw.json. Auth method: LITELLM_API_KEY environment variable.\n\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** (1) Applied the patch to dist/model-preflight.runtime-*.js on the running OpenClaw installation. (2) Waited for the next scheduled cron job run to trigger the preflight probe. (3) Monitored LiteLLM proxy logs via `pm2 logs litellm-proxy`. (4) Monitored OpenClaw gateway logs for cron job execution.\n\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n\n  ![Before/after terminal screenshot](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/samson1357924/openclaw/fix/cron-preflight-clean/evidence-preflight-fix.jpg)\n\n  **Before (top) — no auth header, cron preflight triggers 401:**\n\n  LiteLLM proxy log showing the failed preflight probe:\n  ```text\n  17:30:05 LiteLLM Proxy:ERROR - Exception occured - No api key passed in.\n  Requester IP Address:127.0.0.1\n  127.0.0.1:58244 - \"GET /models HTTP/1.1\" 401 Unauthorized\n  127.0.0.1:50768 - \"POST /chat/completions HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK\n  ```\n\n  Normal inference calls (POST /chat/completions) succeed because they carry the Authorization header - only the preflight probe was missing it.\n\n  **After (bottom) — auth header sent, preflight succeeds:**\n\n  LiteLLM proxy log showing the successful preflight probe:\n  ```text\n  127.0.0.1:45914 - \"GET /models HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK\n  127.0.0.1:49934 - \"POST /chat/completions HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK\n  ```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** GET /models response changed from **401 Unauthorized** to **200 OK**. No more \"No api key passed in\" errors in LiteLLM proxy logs. Cron preflight cache populates correctly (previously every run retried because 401 was treated as \"unavailable\"). Normal inference calls continue to work as before - unchanged.\n\n- **What was not tested:** Non-default cron agent directories. SecretRef-based auth. Authless providers like Ollama (should be unaffected). OAuth/request-header auth profiles.\n\n## CI Status\n\nRebased to latest `upstream/main`. All CI failures are pre-existing flakes in unrelated test areas (resolve-openclaw-ref GITHUB_OUTPUT env var issue, bench-gateway-restart race, test-projects stale file list). None caused by the PR changes.\n\n## Changes\n\n4 files changed (+390/-5):\n- `src/cron/isolated-agent/model-preflight.runtime.ts` - auth refactor\n- `src/cron/isolated-agent/run.ts` - scope passthrough\n- `src/cron/isolated-agent/model-preflight.runtime.test.ts` - 12 tests\n- `evidence-preflight-fix.jpg` - before/after terminal comparison\n\nCloses #83648\n",
